INSERT INTO `wy_posts` VALUES(1321, 1, '2018-06-17 11:17:55', '2018-06-17 11:17:55', 'YORUBA ARE NOT IDOL WORSHIPERS, ODUDUWA CAME FROM SAUDI ARABIA: OLUWO OF IWO HIM OBA DR ABDUL RASHID SAYS,\r\n\r\nWritten by Sheikh ABANIKANNDA,\r\n\r\nWhen I entered the palace on Friday, the monarch asked me if I know the origin of Yoruba. And I answered Baba : \"Ile Ife\". He said \"No\", we came from Saudi Arabia.\r\n\r\nBaba is right. Initially I taught he was asking me of where we came to settle in Iwo.\r\n\r\nODUDUWA CAME FROM SAUDI ARABIA HISTORIANS SAY:\r\n\r\nThe most important among the historians that wrote about the origin of Yoruba is SAMUEL JOHNSON. He opines that we came from Saudi Arabia.\r\n\r\nBABA LATE SHEIKH ADAM AL-ILORIY also confirms it in his books.\r\n\r\nThey believe that about three men left Saudi Arabia passing through Egypt where one of them stopped, another one stopped in Sudan and stayed there and the last one continued his journey until he got to Ife.\r\n\r\nTHERE ARE SOME TRIBES IN SUDAN THAT PUT TRIBAL MARKS LIKE YORUBA\r\n\r\nDuring my Hajj in 2001 I saw them in Saudi Arabia, you must have greeted them (e kaaro sir) before you realise that they are not Yoruba.\r\n\r\nGo to Saudi Arabia you will see it. They are sons and daughters of our great uncles, Sheikh Adam is telling us.\r\n\r\nThen, if it has happened that way, Yoruba are not IDOL WORSHIPERS BECAUSE WE CAME FROM WHERE ALLAH IS WORSHIPED SINCERELY AND FAITHFULLY (MONOTHEISM).\r\n\r\nOba Telu during his address yesterday opined that OGUN, SANGO etc were just important righteous men among Yoruba. Some of them were Royal Fathers. They were just RIGHTEOUS MEN AND NOT gods or semi gods TO BE WORSHIPPED.\r\n\r\nOluwo of Iwo is right. Ogun, Sango etc were just righteous men during their life, but the generations that followed turned them to gods.\r\n\r\nTHE FIRST IDOLS ON EARTH WERE DURING PROPHET NUHA (AS) :\r\n\r\nQ71 Vs 23 mentioned the names of some idols during the life of Prophet Nuh (such as WADAN, SUWA\'AN, YAGHUTHA, YA\'UQAH and NASIRAH) and the commentators of Quri\'an made us to realize that they were the FIRST SET OF IDOLS WORSHIPED ON EARTH BESIDE ALLAH.\r\n\r\nWe also made to understand that they were just righteous men who played very important roles in public life. People came to them for advice. But Saytan, the accursed, came to the generation after them that, for the roles they played, they must IMMORTALIZE THEM by making THEIR STATUES for remembrance, which they did. During that generation they only visited them for remembrance.\r\n\r\nUntil another generation came and Saytan came to them that their forefathers used to worship them.\r\n\r\nThat is the BEGINNING OF IDOL WORSHIPING ON EARTH. Go and read that Qur\'an quoted above. And that is the message Telu is trying to pass across.\r\n\r\nYoruba are not idol worshipers.\r\n\r\nAnd if you, after all this, you still believe in Ogun, Sango etc, that is your problem.\r\n\r\nMy Telu doesn\'t. He has renounced them publicly, and he has nothing to fear.\r\n\r\nAllah says (Q16 Vs 100):\r\n\r\n\"إنما سلطانه على الذين يتولونه والذين هم به مشركون\"\r\n\r\n\"His power (Saytan and his children OGUN, SANGO etc) is only over those who obey and follow him (Saytan and his children) and those who join partners with him (Saytan and his children) to worship anything beside Allah\".\r\n\r\nIf you don\'t believe them, you have nothing to fear.\r\n\r\nOur father, Sheikh Abdul Baqi, after some Ogun worshipers has converted to Islam during his life in a village nearby Iwo, has commanded that their Ogun STONE be brought to his Madrasat. We used it to file our cutlasses when I was there. And we also put our legs on it when we wanted to wash our legs during ablution. May Allah reward Baba Baqi abundantly.\r\n\r\nThis verse is a prayer for ObaTelu. May Almighty Allah protect him for us.\r\n\r\nThe same Allah that protected Sheikh Abdul Baqi will protect our king for us.\r\n\r\nTill when you meet me in another time.\r\n\r\nGood morning Telu 1.<img class=\"size-medium wp-image-1314 aligncenter\" src=\"http://localhost:8888/alwazeer/wp-content/uploads/2018/06/generals-1-225x300.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"225\" height=\"300\" />', 'Blog', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'blog', '', '', '2018-06-17 11:17:55', '2018-06-17 11:17:55', '', 0, 'http://localhost:8888/alwazeer/?page_id=1321', 0, 'page', '', 0);
